to flight status without further delay.

1021
01:14:37.105 --> 01:14:38.815
These proceedings are closed.

1022
01:14:48.075 --> 01:14:50.077
Get him up flying, soon.

1023
01:15:17.104 --> 01:15:19.356
Come on, kid, come on.
Get in there. Engage.

1024
01:15:19.439 --> 01:15:21.608
All right, you got a bogey
at 2 o'clock low, Maverick.

1025
01:15:21.692 --> 01:15:23.694
You got the angle. Piece of cake, pal.

1026
01:15:27.364 --> 01:15:29.616
Take the shot, kid. Take the shot.

1027
01:15:31.159 --> 01:15:33.161
You can engage any time, Maverick.

1028
01:15:44.298 --> 01:15:46.550
- Hey, where the hell are you going?
- It's not good.

1029
01:15:46.675 --> 01:15:48.218
It... It doesn't look good.

1030
01:15:48.302 --> 01:15:49.636
What do you mean,
it doesn't look good?

1031
01:15:49.720 --> 01:15:51.388
It doesn't get to look
any better than that.

1032
01:16:04.192 --> 01:16:06.069
Hey, man, we could've had him.

1033
01:16:06.570 --> 01:16:08.488
Hey, we could've had him, man!

1034
01:16:10.240 --> 01:16:12.826
I will fire
when I am goddamn good and ready!

1035
01:16:13.702 --> 01:16:14.995
You got that?

1036
01:16:33.597 --> 01:16:35.891
He can't get back in the saddle.
Won't engage.

1037
01:16:36.892 --> 01:16:38.393
It's only been a few days.

1038
01:16:39.269 --> 01:16:41.396
You know, he just might
not make it back.

1039
01:16:45.233 --> 01:16:46.610
Keep sending him up.

1040
01:17:06.213 --> 01:17:07.589
Mitchell.

1041
01:17:08.965 --> 01:17:11.051
I'm sorry about Goose.

1042
01:17:14.805 --> 01:17:16.598
Everybody liked him.

1043
01:17:22.437 --> 01:17:23.772
I'm sorry.

1044
01:17:43.625 --> 01:17:45.293
Hi, it's Wolf man.

1045
01:17:48.296 --> 01:17:50.340
Yeah, Maverick just quit.

1046
01:18:12.821 --> 01:18:13.989
Excuse me.

1047
01:18:18.118 --> 01:18:19.161
May I?

1048
01:18:19.661 --> 01:18:21.163
Please.

1049
01:18:29.337 --> 01:18:30.464
Ill...

1050
01:18:30.547 --> 01:18:32.591
I'll have what he's having.

1051
01:18:32.757 --> 01:18:34.050
Hemlock, is it?

1052
01:18:34.968 --> 01:18:36.470
Ice water.

1053
01:18:41.391 --> 01:18:43.643
You weren't gonna say goodbye?

1054
01:18:45.395 --> 01:18:48.356
I heard you got that job in Washington.

1055
01:18:49.274 --> 01:18:51.860
- Congratulations.
- Thanks.

1056
01:18:54.696 --> 01:18:57.365
But I wasn't gonna leave
without saying goodbye.

1057
01:18:57.949 --> 01:18:59.117
Well...

1058
01:19:01.411 --> 01:19:03.246
It's good to see you.

1059
01:19:04.039 --> 01:19:05.290
Thanks.

1060
01:19:07.459 --> 01:19:09.085
Where you going?

1061
01:19:10.295 --> 01:19:12.923
You don't even have a ticket, do you?

1062
01:19:13.798 --> 01:19:17.344
Listen, I've seen all the evidence,
and it's not your responsibility.

1063
01:19:18.762 --> 01:19:20.347
It's not your fault.

1064
01:19:22.224 --> 01:19:24.726
You're one of the best pilots
in the Navy.

1065
01:19:25.977 --> 01:19:29.231
What you do up there, it's dangerous.

1066
01:19:30.815 --> 01:19:32.776
But you've got to go on.

1067
01:19:33.818 --> 01:19:35.862
No, you don't understand.

1068
01:19:36.905 --> 01:19:38.406
When I first met you,

1069
01:19:39.866 --> 01:19:41.910
you were larger than life.

1070
01:19:44.162 --> 01:19:45.580
Look at you.

1071
01:19:47.666 --> 01:19:50.544
You're not gonna be happy
unless you're going Mach 2

1072
01:19:50.627 --> 01:19:52.629
with your hair on fire, you know that.

1073
01:19:52.712 --> 01:19:54.339
No, it's over.

1074
01:19:54.923 --> 01:19:57.634
- It's just over.
- To be the best of the best

1075
01:19:57.717 --> 01:20:00.595
means you make mistakes
and then you go on.

1076
01:20:00.679 --> 01:20:02.055
It's just like the rest of us.

1077
01:20:02.138 --> 01:20:04.140
Oh, you don't think I know that?

1078
01:20:06.601 --> 01:20:08.645
I'm here to help.

1079
01:20:09.854 --> 01:20:12.023
Look, thank you.

1080
01:20:13.608 --> 01:20:17.445
But if I wanted help, really,
I would have asked for it.

1081
01:20:23.827 --> 01:20:25.453
So I'm too late.

1082
01:20:27.581 --> 01:20:29.374
You've already left.

1083
01:20:31.501 --> 01:20:34.170
You didn't learn a damn thing, did you?

1084
01:20:34.838 --> 01:20:36.423
Except to quit.

1085
01:20:39.801 --> 01:20:42.512
You've got that manoeuvre down
real well.

1086
01:20:50.562 --> 01:20:52.480
So long, Pete Mitchell.

1087
01:21:18.798 --> 01:21:20.717
Well, hi, Maverick, come on in.

1088
01:21:21.343 --> 01:21:22.594
- How are you doing?
- Good.

1089
01:21:22.677 --> 01:21:23.845
Really? You sure?
You sure you're feeling

1090
01:21:23.928 --> 01:21:25.472
-okay with everything?
- Oh, I feel great.

1091
01:21:25.555 --> 01:21:27.599
Jamie, come on. Can I get you a drink

1092
01:21:27.682 --> 01:21:29.684
-or anything else like that?
- No, thank you.

1093
01:21:29.768 --> 01:21:30.810
Okay, well, why don't you just...

1094
01:21:30.894 --> 01:21:32.270
- Thank you very much.
-...make yourself comfortable

1095
01:21:32.354 --> 01:21:34.689
-because Mike will be right down, okay?
- Great, thank you.

1096
01:21:54.334 --> 01:21:56.044
I flew with your old man.

1097
01:21:56.294 --> 01:21:58.838
VF-51, the Oriskany.

1098
01:22:01.633 --> 01:22:03.677
You're a lot like he was.

1099
01:22:04.094 --> 01:22:05.637
Only better

1100
01:22:06.971 --> 01:22:08.556
and worse.

1101
01:22:10.058 --> 01:22:12.936
He was a natural heroic
son of a bitch, that one.

1102
01:22:17.565 --> 01:22:19.150
So he did do it right.

1103
01:22:23.863 --> 01:22:25.699
Yeah, he did it right.

1104
01:22:36.042 --> 01:22:38.336
Is that why you fly the way you do?

1105
01:22:38.420 --> 01:22:40.463
Trying to prove something?

1106
01:22:42.549 --> 01:22:44.884
Yeah, your old man did it right.

1107
01:22:46.302 --> 01:22:48.763
What I'm about to tell you is classified.

1108
01:22:48.847 --> 01:22:50.432
It could end my career.

1109
01:22:50.598 --> 01:22:53.309
We were in the worst dogfight
I ever dreamed of.

1110
01:22:54.978 --> 01:22:57.522
Bogies like fireflies all over the sky.

1111
01:22:59.649 --> 01:23:02.652
His F-4 was hit, he was wounded,
but he could've made it back.

1112
01:23:02.736 --> 01:23:05.905
He stayed in it,
saved three planes before he bought it.

1113
01:23:09.117 --> 01:23:10.452
How come I never heard that before?

1114
01:23:10.535 --> 01:23:12.954
Now, that's not something
the State Department tells dependents

1115
01:23:13.037 --> 01:23:15.707
when the battle occurred
over the wrong line

1116
01:23:15.790 --> 01:23:16.958
on some map.

1117
01:23:18.376 --> 01:23:19.794
So you were there?

1118
01:23:20.420 --> 01:23:21.880
I was there.

1119
01:23:22.881 --> 01:23:24.674
What's on your mind?

1120
01:23:25.967 --> 01:23:27.635
My options, sir.

1121
01:23:29.012 --> 01:23:30.054
Simple.

1122
01:23:31.556 --> 01:23:34.017
First, you've acquired enough
points to show up tomorrow

1123
01:23:34.100 --> 01:23:36.311
and graduate with your Top Gun class.

1124
01:23:37.228 --> 01:23:38.646
Or you can quit.

1125
01:23:40.398 --> 01:23:41.858
There'd be no disgrace.

1126
01:23:41.983 --> 01:23:44.152
That spin was hell.
It would've shook me up.

1127
01:23:44.402 --> 01:23:46.070
So you think I should quit?

1128
01:23:46.446 --> 01:23:47.989
I didn't say that.

1129
01:23:49.824 --> 01:23:52.911
The simple fact is,
you feel responsible for Goose,

1130
01:23:52.994 --> 01:23:55.288
and you have a confidence problem.

1131
01:23:56.664 --> 01:23:59.501
Now, I'm not gonna sit here and blow
sunshine up your ass, lieutenant.

1132
01:23:59.918 --> 01:24:03.546
A good pilot is compelled to
always evaluate what's happened.

1133
01:24:04.714 --> 01:24:06.841
So he can apply what he's learned.

1134
01:24:08.009 --> 01:24:09.803
Up there, we gotta push it.

1135
01:24:11.304 --> 01:24:12.639
That's our job.

1136
01:24:15.141 --> 01:24:18.812
It's your option, lieutenant, all yours.

1137
01:24:31.115 --> 01:24:33.117
Sorry to bother you on a Sunday, sir,

1138
01:24:33.201 --> 01:24:35.161
but thank you very much for your time.

1139
01:24:35.245 --> 01:24:37.539
No problem. Good luck.

1140
01:25:26.963 --> 01:25:28.131
Gentlemen...

1141
01:25:28.381 --> 01:25:29.757
- Where's Maverick?
-...here at Top Gun,

1142
01:25:29.841 --> 01:25:31.551
we challenged you
to fly against the very best.

1143
01:25:31.634 --> 01:25:32.802
I don't know where he is.

1144
01:25:32.886 --> 01:25:34.512
Now, we ask you to take
that expertise...

1145
01:25:34.596 --> 01:25:36.222
You know what he's planning to do?

1146
01:25:36.306 --> 01:25:38.391
...And keep the tradition alive.

1147
01:25:38.558 --> 01:25:39.934
Gotta be hard on the guy,
though, you know?

1148
01:25:40.018 --> 01:25:41.394
Good luck.

1149
01:26:12.550 --> 01:26:15.094
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

1150
01:26:16.930 --> 01:26:18.932
- Congratulations.
- Thanks, Mav.

1151
01:26:19.349 --> 01:26:20.558
Sir.

1152
01:26:23.311 --> 01:26:24.354
Gentlemen.

1153
01:26:25.188 --> 01:26:28.107
I hate to break up the party
before it really gets out of hand,

1154
01:26:28.191 --> 01:26:29.525
but there is work to be done.

1155
01:26:29.609 --> 01:26:32.278
Some of you have to
depart immediately.

1156
01:26:32.362 --> 01:26:34.072
We have a crisis situation.

1157
01:26:34.822 --> 01:26:35.990
Ice, Slider.

1158
01:26:36.074 --> 01:26:37.283
Yo.

1159
01:26:37.367 --> 01:26:39.202
- Hollywood, Wolf man.
- Yes, sir.

1160
01:26:40.995 --> 01:26:42.413
Maverick.

1161
01:26:42.497 --> 01:26:43.873
Sir.

1162
01:26:47.627 --> 01:26:50.129
Maverick, you'll get your RIO
when you get to the ship.

1163
01:26:50.713 --> 01:26:52.173
And if you don't,

1164
01:26:53.174 --> 01:26:54.467
give me a call.

1165
01:26:54.550 --> 01:26:55.927
I'll fly With you.

1166
01:26:58.638 --> 01:26:59.764
Sir.

1167
01:27:09.065 --> 01:27:10.108
Gentlemen, this is bull's-eye.

1168
01:27:11.109 --> 01:27:14.696
The communication ship
SS Layton has become disabled

1169
01:27:14.779 --> 01:27:17.115
and has wandered into foreign territory.

1170
01:27:17.198 --> 01:27:19.534
A rescue operation is to begin
within the hour.

1171
01:27:19.617 --> 01:27:22.704
Your mission is to give
air support to that rescue.

1172
01:27:23.871 --> 01:27:25.873
There are MiGs in the area,
and tensions are high.

1173
01:27:25.957 --> 01:27:29.794
If you witness a hostile act,
you will return fire.

1174
01:27:30.962 --> 01:27:33.339
Those MiGs carry
the Exocet anti-ship missile.

1175
01:27:33.423 --> 01:27:36.092
They can fire that missile
from 100 miles away.

1176
01:27:36.467 --> 01:27:38.219
Gentlemen, this is the real thing.

1177
01:27:38.386 --> 01:27:40.596
This is what you've been trained for.

1178
01:27:40.722 --> 01:27:44.559
You are America's best. Make us proud.

1179
01:27:44.642 --> 01:27:46.227
- Ice.
- Yes, sir.

1180
01:27:46.310 --> 01:27:47.395
- Hollywood.
- Yes, sir.

1181
01:27:47.478 --> 01:27:48.563
Sector two.

1182
01:27:48.646 --> 01:27:51.065
And Maverick, you back them up
with Merlin on Ready Five.

1183
01:27:52.692 --> 01:27:54.402
Yes, sir.

1184
01:27:55.528 --> 01:27:56.571
Rise!

1185
01:27:57.947 --> 01:27:59.407
- Excuse me, sir.
- Yes.

1186
01:27:59.907 --> 01:28:02.744
This is not personal,
but with regard to Maverick,

1187
01:28:03.369 --> 01:28:04.662
is he the best backup that...

1188
01:28:04.746 --> 01:28:07.123
I know what's on your mind,
Kazansky, just get on it.

1189
01:29:23.991 --> 01:29:26.160
Mustang, when you get the chance,
can you give me a mode-four check?

1190
01:29:26.244 --> 01:29:29.664
Voodoo one, you've got a pair
of bogies, 12 o'clock, 15 miles.

1191
01:29:29.747 --> 01:29:34.043
Voodoo one, Voodoo one,
090 radar contact 15 miles.

1192
01:29:34.127 --> 01:29:35.795
They're doing 500 knots.

1193
01:29:35.878 --> 01:29:37.171
Roger, that's your bogey.

1194
01:29:40.383 --> 01:29:43.511
Got them dead ahead, 15 miles,
air speed is 600 knots.

1195
01:29:46.764 --> 01:29:48.891
Bogies' air speed, 650.
We're a little close together.

1196
01:29:48.975 --> 01:29:50.351
Let's take a wider split.

1197
01:29:52.186 --> 01:29:54.689
They're at 15,000 feet now,
dead ahead, ten miles.

1198
01:29:54.981 --> 01:29:56.315
Air speed is still increasing.

1199
01:29:56.399 --> 01:29:59.360
Eight hundred knots.
Dead ahead, now, 8 miles.

1200
01:29:59.527 --> 01:30:02.196
- Dead ahead, now, 8 miles.
- Wood, you got them?

1201
01:30:02.280 --> 01:30:03.531
Not yet, I can't see them.

1202
01:30:03.614 --> 01:30:05.408
They must be close,
I'm getting a hard-on.

1203
01:30:12.582 --> 01:30:14.876
Okay, Wood, I'm taking the lead.
Let's identify them.

1204
01:30:14.959 --> 01:30:16.669
Roger, Ice, you got the lead.

1205
01:30:16.752 --> 01:30:18.713
I'm on your left side, a little low.

1206
01:30:20.548 --> 01:30:23.092
- Maverick's up and ready in Alert Five.
- Good, good.

1207
01:30:25.511 --> 01:30:27.221
Hollywood, my bogey's still locked up.

1208
01:30:27.722 --> 01:30:29.223
He's drifting to the left.

1209
01:30:30.391 --> 01:30:32.518
Still manoeuvring, course 090.

1210
01:30:34.228 --> 01:30:37.231
Okay, Wood, let's bring it to the right,
and we'll get a better angle on them.

1211
01:30:46.574 --> 01:30:48.075
Ice, we got a problem here.

1212
01:30:48.159 --> 01:30:49.577
Now I'm breaking out
four aircraft on the radar.

1213
01:30:49.660 --> 01:30:52.163
Not one pair, two pair.
Repeat, four bogies.

1214
01:30:52.246 --> 01:30:53.664
Wood, we've got four bogies.

1215
01:30:56.834 --> 01:30:58.002
Wrong! Make that five!

1216
01:30:58.085 --> 01:30:59.128
There's five, sir.

1217
01:30:59.212 --> 01:31:01.130
- That's five?
- Yes, sir.

1218
01:31:02.924 --> 01:31:04.258
Oh, shit!

1219
01:31:04.884 --> 01:31:06.469
He's got a radar lock on us!

1220
01:31:08.596 --> 01:31:11.515
Get out of there, Hollywood!
Get out of there, goddamn it!

1221
01:31:18.731 --> 01:31:19.857
Break left!

1222
01:31:20.066 --> 01:31:22.318
I'm hit! I'm hit! We're coming apart!

1223
01:31:22.401 --> 01:31:24.111
I can't control it! Hold on!

1224
01:31:24.195 --> 01:31:25.821
Zero for twenty! We're going down!

1225
01:31:25.905 --> 01:31:27.114
Wood's been hit! Wood's been hit!

1226
01:31:27.198 --> 01:31:28.658
Shit! Wood's been hit!

1227
01:31:28.741 --> 01:31:30.868
Voodoo one! Wood's been hit!
Wood's been hit!

1228
01:31:30.952 --> 01:31:33.162
We've lost Hollywood!
Repeat, we've lost Hollywood!

1229
01:31:33.246 --> 01:31:35.831
- We've lost our wingman.
- Launch Maverick on Alert Five.

1230
01:31:35.957 --> 01:31:37.875
Get a bearing on
Hollywood and Wolfman

1231
01:31:37.959 --> 01:31:40.294
and launch the rescue
helicopter immediately.

1232
01:32:07.071 --> 01:32:09.073
- Maverick's airborne.
- Iceman, what's your position?

1233
01:32:09.323 --> 01:32:11.617
090 at 180 miles.

1234
01:32:11.701 --> 01:32:13.494
Yeah, we're coming in left!

1235
01:32:13.828 --> 01:32:15.997
Three MiGs, dead ahead,
coming down the left side.

1236
01:32:18.207 --> 01:32:20.543
I'm going after them.
I'm bringing it around to the left.

1237
01:32:23.421 --> 01:32:26.048
We got four on our tail!
That makes six of them!

1238
01:32:26.132 --> 01:32:28.342
Who do you think is hooking
in the guns range?

1239
01:32:32.847 --> 01:32:34.473
He's firing! Break right!

1240
01:32:36.475 --> 01:32:38.352
Mustang, this is Voodoo one,
we are totally defensive.

1241
01:32:38.436 --> 01:32:39.520
Launch the alert fighters.

1242
01:32:39.603 --> 01:32:40.646
Where? Where are they?

1243
01:32:40.730 --> 01:32:42.773
A hundred and sixty miles
and closing in fast, sir.

1244
01:32:42.857 --> 01:32:45.192
Ready Willard and Simkin
off CATs three and four.

1245
01:32:47.987 --> 01:32:50.239
Maverick's supersonic.
I'll be there in 30 seconds.

1246
01:32:50.323 --> 01:32:52.074
Move your ass! Get up here!
I'm engaged with five.

1247
01:32:52.158 --> 01:32:53.868
Repeat, five. I'm in deep shit!

1248
01:32:56.495 --> 01:32:57.747
What about Willard and Simkin?

1249
01:32:58.539 --> 01:33:01.042
Both catapults are broken.
We can't launch any aircraft yet, sir.

1250
01:33:01.459 --> 01:33:03.044
- How long?
- It'll take ten minutes.

1251
01:33:03.127 --> 01:33:05.463
Bullshit, ten minutes.
This thing will be over in two minutes.

1252
01:33:05.546 --> 01:33:07.048
Get on it!

1253
01:33:08.674 --> 01:33:11.052
One MiG, 12 o'clock high!
One MiG, 12 o'clock high!

1254
01:33:11.719 --> 01:33:13.721
Watch your back! Watch your back!

1255
01:33:18.601 --> 01:33:19.769
Break right!

1256
01:33:22.063 --> 01:33:23.481
Shit, that was close!

1257
01:33:23.606 --> 01:33:24.732
Maverick, how about
some help down here?

1258
01:33:24.815 --> 01:33:27.068
- Where the hell are you?
- Come on, kid, hang in there.

1259
01:33:29.570 --> 01:33:31.072
Jesus Christ.

1260
01:33:33.115 --> 01:33:35.368
Maverick, how about some help?
Engage, goddamn it!

1261
01:33:37.495 --> 01:33:39.830
Maverick, we got a MiG on our tail.

1262
01:33:42.333 --> 01:33:43.876
Watch out! Watch out!

1263
01:33:46.295 --> 01:33:48.672
Shit, we just flew
right through his jet wash.

1264
01:33:50.883 --> 01:33:52.802
Get control, Mav! Get control!

1265
01:34:00.434 --> 01:34:01.811
Good recovery, Mav.

1266
01:34:02.269 --> 01:34:03.813
Okay, let's get in there.

1267
01:34:03.979 --> 01:34:05.731
Come on, we gotta help Ice.

1268
01:34:05.898 --> 01:34:07.900
Come on, let's get back
in the game, Maverick!

1269
01:34:07.983 --> 01:34:10.027
- Come on! Get in there, Maverick!
- No. It's no good.

1270
01:34:10.111 --> 01:34:11.612
It's no good.

1271
01:34:13.781 --> 01:34:15.783
God damn it! Maverick's disengaging!

1272
01:34:15.866 --> 01:34:17.326
I knew it! Shit!

1273
01:34:17.410 --> 01:34:18.869
God damn it, Maverick!

1274
01:34:22.081 --> 01:34:23.624
Get in there, Maverick!
You can't leave him!

1275
01:34:24.959 --> 01:34:26.085
Come on! Maverick!
What the hell are you doing?

1276
01:34:26.168 --> 01:34:27.211
Talk to me, Goose.

1277
01:34:27.294 --> 01:34:28.337
Maverick, get in there, for Christ's sake!

1278
01:34:28.421 --> 01:34:30.423
- Ice is in trouble!
- Talk to me, Goose

1279
01:34:30.506 --> 01:34:32.591
Get in there, Maverick!
He won't last down there alone!

1280
01:34:32.675 --> 01:34:34.135
Get in the fight, for Christ's sake!

1281
01:34:34.218 --> 01:34:36.679
Maverick! Maverick!

1282
01:34:39.515 --> 01:34:41.100
Maverick's reengaging, sir.

1283
01:34:46.897 --> 01:34:49.859
- I can't get him off my tail!
- Ice, I've got your MiG dead ahead.

1284
01:34:49.942 --> 01:34:51.360
I've got him dead ahead.

1285
01:34:52.945 --> 01:34:54.572
Good tone. I've got good tone.

1286
01:34:55.281 --> 01:34:57.158
I've got tone! I've got tone! Firing!

1287
01:35:08.252 --> 01:35:10.671
- Where? Where are they?
- A hundred and fifty-five miles.

1288
01:35:10.838 --> 01:35:13.174
Two MiGs, dead ahead.
Closing at 800 miles an hour.

1289
01:35:13.257 --> 01:35:15.551
I see them. I see them.
I'm gonna take them down the left side.

1290
01:35:17.970 --> 01:35:19.221
Oh, my God.

1291
01:35:22.349 --> 01:35:24.560
Ice is right below us.
He's got a MiG on his tail.

1292
01:35:26.937 --> 01:35:29.023
He's firing! Break left! Break left!

1293
01:35:32.359 --> 01:35:34.487
He overshot! He overshot!

1294
01:35:35.154 --> 01:35:36.864
Coming in, Ice. I'm coming in.

1295
01:35:39.533 --> 01:35:41.035
I got two MiGs dead ahead.

1296
01:35:42.161 --> 01:35:44.371
I got him, Mav.
One MiG passing between us.

1297
01:35:48.834 --> 01:35:51.045
You got a MiG on your left. On your left!
3 o'clock!

1298
01:35:51.128 --> 01:35:52.796
He's gonna fire, he's gonna fire!

1299
01:35:59.970 --> 01:36:01.263
Maverick, check the guys to the north!

1300
01:36:01.347 --> 01:36:02.890
Check the guys to the north!

1301
01:36:05.601 --> 01:36:07.561
Banking left. Banking left.

1302
01:36:10.189 --> 01:36:12.233
There he is. Get him, Ice. Get him!

1303
01:36:12.399 --> 01:36:13.901
Okay, you guys, I'm coming in!

1304
01:36:18.906 --> 01:36:20.574
Maverick, we got a MiG
coming around on our tail!

1305
01:36:20.658 --> 01:36:23.244
- We gotta get out of here!
- I can't leave Ice.

1306
01:36:23.327 --> 01:36:25.746
He's still coming around!
He's gonna get behind us!

1307
01:36:26.205 --> 01:36:27.998
I'm not leaving my wingman.

1308
01:36:31.001 --> 01:36:33.212
I'm on his tail. I'm on his tail.
I'm going for it.

1309
01:36:33.295 --> 01:36:35.214
I'm going for it.
I'm going for the shot right now.

1310
01:36:35.297 --> 01:36:36.924
Roger. Engaged.

1311
01:36:39.093 --> 01:36:40.511
I've got radar lock.

1312
01:36:41.178 --> 01:36:42.972
Good tone. I'm taking a shot.

1313
01:36:43.097 --> 01:36:44.265
Fire!

1314
01:36:48.143 --> 01:36:50.437
- Bingo!
- Wash that sucker, yeah!

1315
01:36:50.521 --> 01:36:52.147
Ice, watch out.
There's a MiG to your right.

1316
01:36:52.231 --> 01:36:53.399
He's firing!

1317
01:36:55.276 --> 01:36:56.610
I'm hit! I'm hit!

1318
01:36:58.779 --> 01:37:00.322
We're hit! We're hit in the right engine!

1319
01:37:00.406 --> 01:37:02.116
I'm shutting it down!
I'm shutting it down!

1320
01:37:06.620 --> 01:37:08.372
Coming in, Ice. Coming in.

1321
01:37:11.834 --> 01:37:14.628
Ice, that bogey's still behind you.
I'm manoeuvring for a shot.

1322
01:37:14.878 --> 01:37:16.630
Stay with him, Mav, stay with him!

1323
01:37:16.714 --> 01:37:18.048
Take the shot! Nail him! Nail him!

1324
01:37:18.132 --> 01:37:19.967
Shit. Ice, I can't get a tone.

1325
01:37:20.050 --> 01:37:22.136
Shoot, Maverick!
I can't get him off my tail!

1326
01:37:26.724 --> 01:37:27.975
Maverick, we're hit! We're hit again!

1327
01:37:28.058 --> 01:37:30.269
It's okay. Both engines are functioning.
We're okay.

1328
01:37:30.352 --> 01:37:32.813
Ice, on the count of three,
break hard right.

1329
01:37:33.772 --> 01:37:34.815
Three,

1330
01:37:34.898 --> 01:37:35.983
two,

1331
01:37:36.066 --> 01:37:37.943
one. Break right!

1332
01:37:40.946 --> 01:37:42.031
Firing!

1333
01:37:45.701 --> 01:37:46.952
Damn it, I missed!

1334
01:37:47.036 --> 01:37:49.788
Don't let him go. Keep on him, Mav.
Keep on him.

1335
01:37:49.872 --> 01:37:51.457
I got him. I got him.

1336
01:37:53.000 --> 01:37:54.585
Here comes a shot.

1337
01:37:59.840 --> 01:38:01.133
Scratch three!

1338
01:38:03.218 --> 01:38:04.678
Maverick, move!
There's a MiG on your tail!

1339
01:38:04.762 --> 01:38:05.971
There's a MiG on your tail!

1340
01:38:06.055 --> 01:38:07.931
We've got a problem here.
We've only got one missile left.

1341
01:38:08.015 --> 01:38:09.725
Approaching 110 miles, sir.

1342
01:38:09.808 --> 01:38:11.018
God damn it.

1343
01:38:11.101 --> 01:38:12.353
I got him! I got him! He's right on us!

1344
01:38:12.436 --> 01:38:13.812
He's between our tails!

1345
01:38:16.732 --> 01:38:18.150
Shit.

1346
01:38:21.445 --> 01:38:23.030
You haven't lost him. He's still with us!

1347
01:38:27.201 --> 01:38:28.661
What are you doing?
You're slowing down!

1348
01:38:28.744 --> 01:38:29.870
You're slowing down!

1349
01:38:29.953 --> 01:38:31.330
I'm bringing him in closer, Merlin.

1350
01:38:31.413 --> 01:38:32.706
You're gonna do what?

1351
01:38:37.670 --> 01:38:39.254
This is it, Maverick!

1352
01:38:39.338 --> 01:38:41.048
I'm gonna hit the brakes,
he'll fly right by.

1353
01:38:41.131 --> 01:38:42.716
Shit! He's gonna get a lock on us!

1354
01:38:46.095 --> 01:38:47.471
Now!

1355
01:38:52.309 --> 01:38:54.561
I got a good lock. Firing.

1356
01:38:59.483 --> 01:39:00.734
Scratch four!

1357
01:39:04.905 --> 01:39:06.740
Mustang, this is Voodoo three.

1358
01:39:06.824 --> 01:39:08.534
Remaining MiGs are bugging out.

1359
01:39:23.507 --> 01:39:26.468
Mustang, this is Maverick
requesting flyby.

1360
01:39:27.511 --> 01:39:29.263
Negative, Ghost Rider.
The pattern is full.

1361
01:39:32.433 --> 01:39:34.143
Excuse me.
Something I should know about?

1362
01:39:46.780 --> 01:39:47.990
Thank you.

1363
01:39:53.412 --> 01:39:55.080
God damn that guy.

1364
01:40:19.104 --> 01:40:20.481
Yes!

1365
01:40:48.175 --> 01:40:50.552
What the hell happened
to you guys? Hollywood!

1366
01:40:51.094 --> 01:40:52.137
You!

1367
01:40:55.933 --> 01:40:57.518
You are still dangerous.

1368
01:41:01.855 --> 01:41:04.066
You can be my wingman anytime.

1369
01:41:05.317 --> 01:41:06.443
Bullshit.

1370
01:41:06.527 --> 01:41:07.903
You can be mine.

1371
01:41:59.997 --> 01:42:01.665
- Maverick.
- Sir.

1372
01:42:01.874 --> 01:42:03.375
How does it feel to be on the front page

1373
01:42:03.458 --> 01:42:04.793
of every newspaper
in the English-speaking world?

1374
01:42:06.044 --> 01:42:07.838
Even though the other side
denies the incident.

1375
01:42:07.921 --> 01:42:09.590
- Congratulations.
- Thank you, sir.

1376
01:42:09.882 --> 01:42:11.258
They gave you your choice of duty, son.

1377
01:42:11.341 --> 01:42:13.176
Anything, anywhere.
Do you believe that shit?

1378
01:42:13.844 --> 01:42:16.388
Where do you think you wanna go?

1379
01:42:16.763 --> 01:42:19.141
I thought of being an instructor, sir.

1380
01:42:20.225 --> 01:42:21.435
Top Gun?

1381
01:42:21.935 --> 01:42:23.061
Yes, sir.

1382
01:42:23.645 --> 01:42:24.813
God help us.

1383
01:43:45.394 --> 01:43:46.395
Hello, Pete Mitchell.

1384
01:43:52.067 --> 01:43:54.194
I heard the best of the best
were gonna be back here,

1385
01:43:54.277 --> 01:43:55.821
SO...

1386
01:44:01.076 --> 01:44:02.744
This could be complicated.

1387
01:44:04.746 --> 01:44:08.583
You know, on the first one,
I crashed and burned.

1388
01:44:10.168 --> 01:44:11.253
And the second?

1389
01:44:18.677 --> 01:44:19.928
I don't know,

1390
01:44:21.096 --> 01:44:25.100
but it's looking good so far.

